In the final season (Season 8) of the HBO series Game of Thrones, Daenerys' character takes a dramatic turn.

After liberating King's Landing from Cersei Lannister's tyranny, Daenerys becomes increasingly unhinged and begins to exhibit signs of madness, much like her father, Aerys II Targaryen (also known as the Mad King).
As she tries to take control of the city, Daenerys orders her dragon, Drogon, to burn everything to ashes, despite the surrender of the enemy forces.
As she prepares to rule Westeros, Daenerys starts to display a desire for absolute power and control.
She orders the burning of King's Landing with dragonfire, despite the city's people surrendering to her.
She becomes more isolated and paranoid, surrounding herself only with loyal followers who fear to question her decisions.
She becomes isolated and paranoid, surrounding herself only with those who blindly follow her orders, while pushing away those who advise caution, such as Jorah Mormont and Tyrion Lannister.
She orders her dragon, Drogon, to burn King's Landing to ashes, killing thousands of innocent civilians, including women and children.
She burns King's Landing to ashes using her dragon, Drogon, killing thousands of innocent people, including women and children.
She becomes isolated from her advisors, including Tyrion Lannister and Jon Snow, who try to counsel her on more benevolent paths.
She orders the burning of King's Landing, even after the city has surrendered, killing thousands of innocent civilians, including women and children.
She burns King's Landing to ashes, killing thousands of innocent civilians, including women and children, using her dragon, Drogon.
She becomes paranoid and isolated, surrounding herself only with people who agree with her.
She becomes isolated and paranoid, refusing to listen to advice from her trusted advisors, including Jorah Mormont, Tyrion Lannister, and Jon Snow (Aegon Targaryen, her secret nephew).
She becomes isolated from her advisors and friends, surrounding herself with yes-men who are too afraid to question her actions.
She burns the fleet sent by Euron Greyjoy to attack King's Landing, and then proceeds to raze the city to the ground using her dragon, Drogon.
She orders her dragon, Drogon, to burn down entire city blocks and kill innocent civilians, marking a departure from her initial goal of breaking the wheel and freeing the people.
